title: Austria Imports
description: Imports in Austria increased to 16831 EUR Million in August from 16470 EUR Million in July of 2022. Imports in Austria averaged 4453.89 EUR Million from 1953 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 19472 EUR Million in March of 2022 and a record low of 61 EUR Million in January of 1953. Austria imports mainly machinery and equipment, motor vehicles, chemicals, metal goods, oil and oil products and foodstuffs. Its main import partners are European Union countries (Germany, Italy, Netherlands), Switzerland, China and United States. This page provides - Austria Imports - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Oesterreichische National Bank
